<p>Nearly 90% of ChatGPT citations come from URLs ranked position 21 or lower in Google. Brand search volume, not backlinks, is the strongest predictor of whether an AI model mentions your brand. And 70% of AI-generated content changes between repeated runs of the same query.</p>
<p>LLM visibility is the new metric that determines whether your business exists in the AI-first search era. Traditional SEO tells you where you rank on Google. LLM visibility tells you what ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, and Claude say about you when someone asks a question.</p>
<p>The difference matters. Search engine volume is expected to drop <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/llm-visibility/">25% by 2026</a> as users shift to AI assistants. The brands that show up in AI answers capture the attention. The ones that do not become invisible.</p>
<p>We have published 3,500+ SEO articles across 70+ industries and tracked how AI models cite, describe, and recommend brands. This guide explains what LLM visibility is, why it matters, how AI models decide what to cite, and what you can do about it.</p>
